Time Series Analysis and Models

amazon.stock = df %>% filter(Stock == "Amazon") %>% arrange(Date)
ggtsdisplay(amazon.stock %>% select(diff), main = "Close Price")

ts.model = auto.arima(amazon.stock %>% select(diff), seasonal = TRUE)
ggtsdisplay(ts.model$residuals, main = "Arima(3, 0, 4)")

ts.model %>% summary()
## Series: amazon.stock %>% select(diff) 
## ARIMA(3,0,4) with zero mean 
## 
## Coefficients:
##          ar1      ar2      ar3      ma1     ma2     ma3      ma4
##       0.7299  -0.8098  -0.1214  -0.7095  0.6791  0.1926  -0.0543
## s.e.  0.3378   0.3040   0.3086   0.3378  0.2937  0.2757   0.0292
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 26.35:  log likelihood=-16088.56
## AIC=32193.11   AICc=32193.14   BIC=32245.67
## 
## Training set error measures:
##                      ME     RMSE     MAE MPE MAPE      MASE         ACF1
## Training set 0.02473124 5.129765 2.54636 NaN  Inf 0.7041326 4.123699e-05
amazon.stock = amazon.stock %>% mutate(ts.residuals = ts.model$residuals)

res.lm.model = lm(data = amazon.stock, formula = ts.residuals ~ Open + Volume)
res.lm.model %>% summary()
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = ts.residuals ~ Open + Volume, data = amazon.stock)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -85.737  -1.105  -0.037   1.080  70.651 
## 
## Coefficients:
##               Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)
## (Intercept)  1.590e-02  1.246e-01   0.128    0.898
## Open        -3.485e-04  2.523e-04  -1.381    0.167
## Volume       1.030e-08  9.682e-09   1.063    0.288
## 
## Residual standard error: 5.129 on 5265 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.0007799,  Adjusted R-squared:  0.0004003 
## F-statistic: 2.055 on 2 and 5265 DF,  p-value: 0.1282
amazon.stock = amazon.stock %>% 
  mutate(ts.pred = ts.model$fitted + res.lm.model$fitted.values)
amazon.stock$residuals = c(amazon.stock$Close - amazon.stock$ts.pred)

ggplot(data = amazon.stock, aes(x = Date)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = Close, color = "red")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = Open + ts.pred, color = "blue")) +
  xlab("time") +
  ylab("Close Price of Amazon Stock") +
  ggtitle("ARIMA(3, 0, 4)")

rmse(amazon.stock$diff, amazon.stock$naive.pred)
## [1] 5.20788
rmse(amazon.stock$diff, amazon.stock$ts.pred)
## [1] 5.127704
